<div class="consent-text">
  <p>Thank you for agreeing to participate in this research study. Please read the following information carefully before proceeding.</p>
  <h3>About the study</h3>
  <p>This study is conducted by Filip Olsson at the European University Institute (EUI). It examines how media coverage of climate change influences public attitudes, behavioural intentions, and policy preferences. The study is funded by the Magnus Bergvall Foundation.</p>
  <h3>What you will do</h3>
  <p>You will read a short news article and then answer a series of questions about your views on climate change. The survey takes approximately 8 to 12 minutes to complete.</p>
  <h3>Your rights</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Participation is voluntary. You may withdraw at any time without penalty.</li>
    <li>Your responses are anonymous. Individual data cannot be linked to you after collection.</li>
    <li>You may withdraw your data within 30 days by emailing filip.olsson@eui.eu with your Prolific ID. After 30 days the dataset is fully anonymised and individual responses can no longer be located.</li>
  </ul>
  <h3>Contact</h3>
  <p>Study questions: filip.olsson@eui.eu &nbsp;|&nbsp; Ethics questions: ethics@eui.eu &nbsp;|&nbsp; Data protection: data_protection_officer@eui.eu</p>
